[3] Iowa
Date: Thu 27 Sep 2018
Source: The Horse [edited]
https://thehorse.com/161092/wnv-in-iowa-horses-two-new-cases-confirmed/


The Equine Disease Communication Center (EDCC) reported [Wed 26 Sep 2018] that the Iowa state veterinarian has confirmed 2 new equine West Nile virus (WNV) cases. There have been 10 confirmed cases of WNV in Iowa horses so far this year [2018], according to EDCC data.

"On 20 Sep 2018, an 18-year-old Belgian gelding in Clinton County had facial and chest muscle fasciculation (twitching), stiffness in the legs, muscle weakness in the hind limbs, ataxia (incoordination), and mild fever," the EDCC said.

Meanwhile, "a 3-year-old Quarter Horse mare in Wapello County was examined on 23 Sep 2018," the EDCC said. "The horse 1st developed posterior paresis on 22 Sep 2018 and progressed to being recumbent the next day. The horse was treated symptomatically, examined the following day [23 Sep 2018], and the owner elected to humanely euthanize on 24 Sep 2018. This mare was not vaccinated for WNV this year [2018] and had no previous history of WNV vaccination."

Last year [2017] there were 2 confirmed cases of WNV in Iowa horses, according to USDA Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service data.

[Byline: Erica Larson]

