[How tragic to have so many horses affected and/or euthanized/dead because of a preventable disease! West Nile virus is preventable with a vaccine. The vaccine is usually combined with eastern equine encephalitis and western equine encephalitis and often tetanus. Therefore, a lot of protection for the horse for a very small amount of money. So why are people still not vaccinating? Responsibility for having an animal as a working animal or as a companion, regardless of size, means taking the responsibility of protecting the animal. - Mod.TG

